

           A Landscape design program for A3Dsimple-sim
          .. but it can be interesting just to play with...


 Requires  A1200.    A500 1mb should work but since it  uses 3d for all
operations it would be pretty slow.



The archive includes:-
- a compiled workbench version for non-amos users.
- amos source code..   for  users  with the 'Voodoo' 3d extension.
- the necessary data banks, 3d objects.
                                                  

The program  expects all the above archive to be 'extracted'  with it's
sub directories  into the same  main directory (any name)

 Done on PAL ,  NTSC  loses screen portion as  screens had to be maximum
to  get stuff in.   Sorry, I believe it's possible to switch fully to pal
from amos Ntsc.   But I don't know, and havn't time left, to find the
 last bits of info..
On A1200 use the boot select to get PAL.. and thence full screens.


     This is a rush upload.(. due to possibility  of being cut off from
internet  by provider cahnges) but the program seems to run Ok.
So in case of a problem, - if the  e-mail address gets no response -
    try posting to:-

